    "question_id": "Q2",
    "framework": "CAIQ",
    "text": "Are independent audit and assurance assessments conducted according to relevant standards at least annually?"
  },
  "outbound_response": "Yes. BNY's financial statements and internal control over financial reporting are subject to an independent annual audit by KPMG LLP, an independent public accounting firm registered with the PCAOB that complies with the auditing, quality control and independence standards and rules of the PCAOB and the SEC. The Audit Committee of the Board has direct responsibility for the selection, appointment, compensation, retention and oversight of the independent registered public accountants engaged to prepare audit reports or to perform other audit, review or attestation services, and annually evaluates KPMG, including its qualifications and independence. Each year the Committee discusses with KPMG the matters required to be communicated under PCAOB Auditing Standard, Communications with Audit Committees, receives the written disclosures and letter required by applicable PCAOB standards regarding auditor independence, and holds a discussion with KPMG regarding its independence. On the basis of these annual reviews, the Audit Committee recommends inclusion of the audited financial statements in BNY's Annual Report.",
